explanation: This solution uses a loop that increments by 5 each time, effectively counting the number of multiples of 5 in the range from 5 to n. This approach is efficient because it only requires a single pass through the range, and it takes advantage of the fact that the number of trailing zeros in n! is determined by the number of factors of 5 in the prime factorization of n!. The time complexity is logarithmic because the loop runs until i > n, which happens when i is a power of 5.

